Sometimes all you need is a little 💗TLC💗to get the “body of your dreams” ✨ I’m sure you hear&read all about it… be more compassionate with yourself, have more self love, get to know yourself better…
But the truth is there is nothing more powerful than the words and thoughts you produce for yourself!
Your words have energy and power with the ability to help, to heal, to hinder, to hurt, to harm, to humiliate, and to humble…so choose them wisely! 
It wasn’t until I became more patient with myself and paid more attention to my mental health over physical to feel my very best. I had to really train myself to just slow things down (my thoughts, really.. and i do this through meditation/breathing) and overtime I was able to sit back & listen to the crazy stories I kept telling myself. If you suffer from mind chatter, it can be difficult to realize that our thoughts don’t define who/what we are because it’s more comfortable to sit & simmer in them. 💭 🤯 👎🏽 
When you train yourself to slow down you can start to take the passenger seat and just observe your thoughts and then pick & choose those that serve you! I promise it can be as simple as it sounds. Just takes practice. 

ℹ️ Some ways I help reprogram my brain is listening to affirmations of how I see my most desired self; I have been using @risinghigherjessshepherd (#risinghighermeditation on YT) for years now and she offers a plethora of wonderfully guided meditations and affirmations with the most soothing voice 😌 (thanks Jess!)
The goal to reprogramming your brain is repetition of this positive reinforcement and doing it first thing after waking or right before bed where brainwaves change & are going through a theta state. ❗️Your mind is PROGRAMMABLE in this relaxed state. ‘When you repeatedly guide your thoughts & beliefs in a direction you want to go in life, your actions and manifestations will automatically follow. 

“Words are seeds that do more than blow around. They land in our hearts and not the ground. Be careful what you plant and careful what you say. You might have to eat what you planted one day.”
Trust, believe, succeed #imaginarymagnitude #brainreprogramming #createthelifeyouwant ✨🧠🌎

On a scale of 1-10, how confident are you in life? What if I told you that “Life will give you whatever experience is most helpful for the evolution of your consciousness.” (E Tolhart)

Ask yourself how that experience is benefitting you or teaching you a lesson. What if you convinced yourself every experience was carefully selected for you in order to guide you in the most efficient way… sometimes it doesn’t make sense in the making but if you keep your mind & heart open you understand it in retrospect. you really can change your perspectives if you truly desired to. 
Looking at life in this spectrum allows you to feel excitement about the unknown, because you trust that God & the Universe will take you exactly where you belong. Even in the most dark, discomforting times you can find hope to just keep pushing forward because you find value in your contrast. Your contrast and intuition will be your biggest guides in life! 
This is the only way I chose to view my life. Otherwise I would constantly be a victim of my own thoughts and society’s persuasions. Do I have moments of uncertainty that don’t feel good? Absolutely, I’m only human… but my human self also has the ability to view things differently in a matter of seconds. And that’s the difference between how you chose to live life and how life can outlive you. 
THE MAGIC IS ALL WITHIN YOU ✨ abracadabra the bullshit out of here and anything else that is out of your hands deserves freedom from your mind as well. 🕊️ 

#shiftyourperspective #lifelessons #freeyourmind

“I should start eating better. But I can’t, because I have that big social event coming up. Oh, and I’ve got drinks with Jessica the week after…” 
The biggest problem with these thoughts is it begins to move the starting line, which is the idea that the journey to improve your health & your life are two separate things. 📰 NEWS FLASH: They aren’t! 
People with healthy habits don’t maintain them by becoming hermits; they combine their social life and their healthy decisions, using social commitments as a way to stay on track rather than getting OFF track…

#dieting ignores the fact that food plays a central role in how we connect with others.
Since the earliest of days, food & social connection are deeply connected, and dieting serves as a barrier between the two. If your goal for losing weight is health related & your diet is socially isolating, then it is no longer serving your goal.

If your goal for losing weight is appearance and your diet has become socially isolating, who will even see you?
Learn to have balance with your health goals and social life. You don’t have to skip brunch with the girls! But you also don’t have to go overboard. 
Any time someone suggests, “Hey let’s go get drinks,” or “Let’s go out for dinner,” the goal is to still say YES and then you can suggest healthy restaurant or activity. 
You may be surprised to find out all of your friends will want to do the healthiest version of whatever they suggested, they just couldn’t think of any alternatives! 

My favorite way to stay healthy and socialize is usually by beginning the day with some physical activity, whether it’s a fitness class we attend together or hit a hiking trail or a beach, workout, etc. and then go out for brunch afterwards to reward ourselves for the work we put in :-) 

You got this !! 👏🏽

An oldie but a goodie… a crazy event happened this day. A testimony to my faith in God as a matter of fact. 
I was digging through my bag of clothes to change for my next look when I saw a small pendant of Jesus laying on top. I asked my girl who was shooting me, “is this yours?” And she said “I’ve never owned anything like that”, and I never have owned one either. It was the strangest thing. Meanwhile my car is about to get towed across the street so I *secured* it in my pants pocket and took off to save my car. Later on that evening I had a client out in Redondo so I get to the parking garage & decided to have a moment with my finding. Come to find out the pendant suddenly DISAPPEARED out of nowhere, there was no way that thing fell out because I secured it for sure. I started panicking because i kept thinking “no! I NEED YOU!” And after not finding it i enter the gym & my client tells me hey, you don’t look so good like you just saw a ghost or something. Let’s go talk” etc. I was really struggling at this time of my life. I had just moved to LA pretty recently. So I took it as a sign that He is always by my side even when I feel like He’s out of reach. 
You’ll never believe.. when things finally turned around for me 2 years later I found what seemed to be the same exact pendant at a gas station… just sitting there in the ground. It shined in the sun and that’s how it caught my attention. I instantly started balling, being grateful for everything I had in that moment because of Him. I left it there for someone else to find bc I received my message. 
Trust & Believe. Pray when you feel lost lonely frustrated stressed… trust in His plan🙏🏼

Add these 5 #core moves to the end of your next workout! 
:40s on :10s rest in between, 3-4 rounds 🔥 

Cues:
1. keep elbow aligned with your shoulders, keep hips pushed up
2. Stay hollow, preferably keep lower back in contact with the floor 
3. Pull straight leg up as high as possible, hands on floor 
4. Start sitting up, then lean back into a hollow position & BREATHE. Keep lower back in contact with floor for more of a challenge 
5. limbs stay extended, lift shoulders off ground 
6. Keep arms straight & hips extended 
*Always exhale on the “crunch” part of the exercise!

Part I of my #SintMaarten 🇸🇽 trip…. This is just a reel of my sisters amazing new condo in #GuanaBay & her neighborhood… it’s so up my sister’s alley (& mine!!) and I’m so happy for her! 😃 I mean, look at this beautiful island! And her view is priceless 🫰🏽 that’s St. Bartholomew Island across the way (Jeff Bezos and the like party at this island) and anyone who resides or rents here gets access to that private beach right below 🙌🏽 🏖️ i was in heaven !! Definitely a place to add to your bucket list if you haven’t been here yet! The island itself is only 37 miles and has a total of 37 beaches, one side is French and the other side is Dutch (where my sister lives). The biggest difference between the two sides is currency- Dutch use dollars and their own (guilders) while French use euros, electricity- on the French side you have to use a converter for all your electronics like you’re in Europe, and the language primarily used on the Dutch side is English while the other is French. It’s Pretty interesting to have so much going on a little island 🏝️!! But the best part about this island is how friendly everyone is (the locals!) 🥹🥰 so much love and respect for everyone that surrounds them and keeps their island running 💗
